<div id="outline-container-org57fd7d1" class="outline-2">
<h2 id="org57fd7d1">Redis&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;<span class="tag"><span class="database">database</span>&#xa0;<span class="db">db</span>&#xa0;<span class="redis">redis</span></span></h2>
<div class="outline-text-2" id="text-org57fd7d1">
<p>
Redis is a in memeory key-value dataabase. Since it is a nosql database it can do a number of things.
</p>

<p>
It is commonly used as a cache system or a task queue.
</p>


<p>
Redis stands for remote dictionary server.
</p>
</div>

<div id="outline-container-org299a208" class="outline-3">
<h3 id="org299a208">Topics</h3>
<div class="outline-text-3" id="text-org299a208">
<ul class="org-ul">
<li><a href="20230330161754-redis_expiration.html#ID-d7ec3a25-ea89-4ab5-ac11-dd4fd05f94a9">redis expiration</a></li>
<li></li>
</ul>
</div>
</div>
<div id="outline-container-orgf171003" class="outline-3">
<h3 id="orgf171003">Storage and Retrieval</h3>
<div class="outline-text-3" id="text-orgf171003">
<p>
Like other key value databases.
All keys are strings.
Data is Accessed by keys.
</p>

<p>
Keys exists in a "key" space (think database)
Single commands are atomic.
</p>
</div>
</div>


<div id="outline-container-orgdbaa033" class="outline-3">
<h3 id="orgdbaa033">Data Types</h3>
<div class="outline-text-3" id="text-orgdbaa033">
</div>
<div id="outline-container-orgcb25d7d" class="outline-4">
<h4 id="orgcb25d7d">String</h4>
<div class="outline-text-4" id="text-orgcb25d7d">
<p>
Normal sequence of bytes. They are binary safe, so they are not null terminated.
</p>
</div>
</div>
<div id="outline-container-org3f5fb15" class="outline-4">
<h4 id="org3f5fb15">Hashes</h4>
<div class="outline-text-4" id="text-org3f5fb15">
<p>
Represents a collection of key val pairs
</p>

<p>
The command prefixes start with H
</p>
</div>
</div>
</div>


<div id="outline-container-org01a1525" class="outline-3">
<h3 id="org01a1525">Commands</h3>
<div class="outline-text-3" id="text-org01a1525">
<p>
I will not list all the commands here, just the most used ones
</p>
</div>

<div id="outline-container-org9982358" class="outline-4">
<h4 id="org9982358">SET</h4>
<div class="outline-text-4" id="text-org9982358">
<p>
Set is used to set a key to a value
</p>

<div class="org-src-container">
<pre class="src src-shell"><span style="font-weight: bold;">set</span> name foo
</pre>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<div id="outline-container-org1775710" class="outline-4">
<h4 id="org1775710">GET</h4>
<div class="outline-text-4" id="text-org1775710">
<p>
Get is used to get a key's value
</p>
<div class="org-src-container">
<pre class="src src-shell">get name
</pre>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<div id="outline-container-org3f7cfd5" class="outline-4">
<h4 id="org3f7cfd5">Del</h4>
<div class="outline-text-4" id="text-org3f7cfd5">
<p>
Del removes a key
</p>
<div class="org-src-container">
<pre class="src src-shell">del name
</pre>
</div>
</div>
</div>

<div id="outline-container-org55467c7" class="outline-4">
<h4 id="org55467c7">GETSET</h4>
<div class="outline-text-4" id="text-org55467c7">
<p>
Get a key's value and set a new one
</p>
<div class="org-src-container">
<pre class="src src-shell">getset name foo
</pre>
</div>
<div class="org-src-container">
<pre class="src src-shell">setset name foo1
</pre>
</div>
<p>
If you ran it one more time you would get foo1
</p>
</div>
</div>
<div id="outline-container-org4dd55db" class="outline-4">
<h4 id="org4dd55db">SETNX</h4>
<div class="outline-text-4" id="text-org4dd55db">
<p>
Set a key if its non existent (is this a lock?)
</p>

<div class="org-src-container">
<pre class="src src-shell">setnx name bar
</pre>
</div>
<p>
#+RESULTS
</p>
<pre class="example">
(integer) 0
</pre>


<p>
See since name exists it failed to set the key
</p>


<div class="org-src-container">
<pre class="src src-shell">setnx name1 bar
</pre>
</div>
<p>
#+RESULTS
</p>
<pre class="example">
(integer) 1
</pre>
</div>
</div>
</div>


<div id="outline-container-org258cff0" class="outline-3">
<h3 id="org258cff0">Atomic Commands</h3>
<div class="outline-text-3" id="text-org258cff0">
<p>
A atomic command is one that can take multiple keys and values and do it in a all or fail manner
</p>

<p>
They operate the same except have a m added to the name
so <code>mset</code> would be <code>set</code>.
</p>

<p>
<code>del</code> can take multiple keys
</p>
